title: Lions OG Warford inactive; Dallas QB Cassel active vs. Pats
text:
By The Associated Press
There are all sorts of injury issues and key inactive players for the Detroit Lions, the NFL's only team without a victory heading into Week 5.
Before hosting the Arizona Cardinals on Sunday, Detroit's struggling offensive line took a hit when guard Larry Warford was put on the inactive list with an ankle injury after being listed as questionable.
The Lions previously had ruled out running back Joique Bell (ankle), tight end Eric Ebron (knee) and defensive tackle Haloti Ngata (calf).
Detroit's defense did get a boost with the return of linebacker DeAndre Levy (hip), ready to play for the first time this season after being sidelined by a hip injury.
Dallas has quarterback Matt Cassel active for the first time since the Cowboys got him in a trade from Buffalo last month - so he'll be available against New England, his former team.
The Raiders, hosting Denver, have safety TJ Carrie active even though he didn't practice all week because of a chest injury. Carrie was initially ruled out on Friday, then was listed as questionable on Saturday, before being in uniform on Sunday.
